trend_summary: Across the series, modest farmland expansion and a few new roads and structures cluster near the dam, while reservoir shorelines fluctuate with water levels. Southern wooded hills stay largely intact, with only slight edge thinning. Change is gradual, and settlement remains sparse within a predominantly rural landscape.
notable_changes: Incremental enlargement of crop fields in the northern plateau, replacing pockets of grassland.
Small cluster of new buildings and paved areas near the dam outlet.
Additional feeder roads connecting northern farms to the main route.
Visible year-to-year fluctuation of reservoir shoreline indicating water-level changes.
Minor thinning of forest edges along eastern slopes, but core woodland conserved.
